    "summary": "Currently a Principal Engineering Manager at bol.com, where I lead 5 Engineering Managers within the FinTech domain (4 products / 65 employees) to make bol.com platform even more innovative and convenient. I'm proud to manage the tech leadership team. Together with my counterparts we work on understanding our employees needs and bringing people, tech and customer value in fuzzy-middle of our domain. Herein specifically, I'm an passionate leader with experience both on the product and engineering side. Combining my business background, tech interest, and broad experience with(in) software development (leadership and product) teams to create domains, were employees love to work and were products are building features that our customers love. Whomever that employee or customer might be!\n\nWorked with a very wide variety of (leadership-/product)teams, both in scope and nature. From technical platform teams to teams that work on consumer-facing products. Within the projects I have done, I have performed in a variety of roles such as Product Manager, Business Analyst, Technical Product Owner, Business Product Owner, CTO, Business Developer, Tech Lead, and Process/Information Analyst. I have developed myself in Scrum, people management, implementing new processes and strategies, mentoring developers and coaching new managers for these teams.\n\nMy main achievements are setting up a new business model or development team from scratch, move things forward by giving the right guidance, finding the right people and implement the different disciplines within one team.\n\nSome examples are:\n\u2726 Co-founder Select Subscription model; \ndevelop customer proposition. Manage business case & commercial negotiations. IT & operational implementation for free shipping subscription model\n\u2726 Building Development FinTech teams;\nnew development team with all the processes and tools involved like Atlassian Ecosystem, git/scrum procedures etc.\n\u2726 Leading Young Professional Program;\nLeading and setting-up a Young Professional program from recruitment to graduation\n\nLove to inspire others and get a conversation going with passionate people. Experience as a speaker, active as an entrepreneur, sharing knowledge about various topics that interest me, from customer obsession to organizational setup.\n\nTechnical experience:\nJira \u2503 Gitlab \u2503 SQL\u2503 Java \u2503 Sybase \u2503 Google G-suite admin \u2503 BizzDesigner \u2503 Visual Basic \u2503 TopDesk \u2503 Cognos\n\nLast but definitely not least, I'm always in for a chat, so if there's any reason for you to invite me, never hesitate!",
