                    "description": "I'm the Engineering Manager for 5 teams/29 engineers that work within the FinTech domain (this includes Fraud & Risk, Payments, Invoicing and Collection). I've transformed team to cross-functional product teams, from data science to back-end, to front-end. \n\nMy responsibilities are 4-fold: \n1. Technical Vision & Strategy. setting up a long term vision with the different product teams and guide them during implementation.\n2. People management, from recruiting to hiring, but most time spent on the coaching of soft and hard skills in between, career advancement and well being. \n3. Team management, from topologies and structuring, to ensuring well-ran teams that are capable of delivering high-quality software products. Agile and product transformation of the teams.\n4. Deliver / Technical accountability, from SLIs and SLOs to ensuring proper code quality and best practices\n\nI work with a variety of disciplines and set the technical strategy and vision for my teams, which are cascaded from the board. I have a passion for bridging the technical capabilities and needs to the business goals and roadmaps. \n\nI'm involved in IT-wide and organisation-wide projects regarding structuring of our IT strategy (OGSM) process, leading the Young Professional program and emboldening our engineering culture. I work closely with recruitment to continuously improve our processes and remuneration policy. \n\nI'm an executive sponsor for acquisition and implementation of IT-wide systems, used by 1300+ tech personnel, 3000+ total at bol.com and 17M customers.",
